Key takeaways from the dashboard:

ROC curve shows excellent separation — a 0.94 AUC means the model correctly ranks a recommender above a non-recommender 94% of the time.
Confusion matrix shows the model is especially strong at catching true recommendations (recall 89%), while flagging non-recommendations reasonably well (recall 83%).
Top features: Words like love, perfect, flattering strongly predict recommendations, while disappointed, returned, tight pull toward non-recommendation — exactly what you'd expect.
Class imbalance (82% recommend vs 18% not): handled via class_weight="balanced" to avoid the model just predicting "recommend" for everything.
